# REST API Fundamentals

This repository explains REST API fundamentals from basic to advanced level with real-world frontend–backend examples.

##  Topics Covered

### 1. REST Basics
- What is REST
- Stateless architecture
- Resource-based URLs
- Client–Server separation

### 2. HTTP Methods
- GET – Fetch data
- POST – Create data
- PUT – Update entire resource
- PATCH – Partial update
- DELETE – Remove resource

### 3. HTTP Status Codes
- 2xx – Success responses
- 4xx – Client-side errors
- 5xx – Server-side errors

### 4. Error Handling
- Standard error response structure
- Backend error handling
- Frontend error consumption

### 5. Frontend–Backend Model Alignment
- Consistent data contracts
- Avoiding response mismatches
- Best practices for scalable APIs

##  Tech Stack Examples
- Frontend: React / JavaScript
- Backend: Node.js / Express
- Data Format: JSON

